other_tests.findings: Mild bibasilar atelectasis; liver demonstrates homogenous attenuation; hypodensity adjacent to the falciform ligament likely perfusional; no intrahepatic or extrahepatic biliary dilatation; normal pancreas, spleen, and adrenal glands; kidneys of normal size with normal nephrogram; dilated appendix up to 12 mm with proximal mucosal hyperenhancement and surrounding fat stranding; trace free fluid in the pelvis.
